                    <h2>FAQ</h2>
                    <em>Expand All</em>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="vm-que-pro">If my deployed instance is in the “stopped” state, am I still billed?</a>
                                <section>
                                    <p>Yes. A stopped instance still occupies the computing resources that provide support for the instance, so you will still be charged. In order to stop billing, you need to delete your deployment.</p>
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <i class="icon icon-plus"></i>
                            <div>
                                <a id="vm-que-down">If my web or worker role was deployed for less than an hour, how much will I be charged?</a>
                                <section>
                                    <p>Cloud Services are billed based on the length of time your service was deployed for. If your instance was deployed for less than 1 hour, or several hours plus some minutes that do not add up to 1 hour, you will be charged only for that duration. Azure does not round up partial hours to full hours for billing – you only need to pay for the actual time that your Cloud Services instance was in a “running” state.</p>
                                </section>

                            </div>
                        </li>
